widgets.markdown: # What is it? Dynatrace is a global technology company that provides a software observability platform based on artificial intelligence (AI) and automation. This platform is designed to monitor, analyze, and optimize application performance, software development, security practices, IT infrastructure, and user experience for businesses and government agencies1. Key features of Dynatrace include: - **AI-Powered Monitoring**: Uses a proprietary AI engine called Davis to automatically discover, map, and monitor applications, microservices, and IT infrastructure. - **Unified Observability**: Integrates application performance monitoring (APM), infrastructure monitoring, digital experience management, and business analytics. - **Automation**: Provides automated problem remediation and IT operations analytics. - **Cloud Native Support**: Supports multicloud, hybrid-cloud, and hyperscale network environments. - **Custom Applications**: Allows building custom applications and automated DevOps workflows using its AppEngine and AutomationEngine12. Dynatrace helps organizations manage the complexities of modern cloud environments and supports digital transformation initiatives # For more information: - Contact/Expert: #IS -Site Reliability Engineering - Stack Overflow: View tagged items (or search by "dynatrace" instead) - Access: Dynatrace - Prod, Dynatrace - NonProd - Additional links: Vendor documentation, Dynatrace University

widgets.markdown: # What is it? The GitHub Copilot extension is an AI pair programmer tool that helps you write code faster and smarter. You can use the Copilot extension in Visual Studio Code (VS Code) to generate code, learn from the code it generates, and even configure your editor. GitHub Copilot can provide assistance in a variety of scenarios: - Get code suggestions as you type - Make large changes across multiple files - Ask questions about your code - Refactor and improve your code - Fix code issues and debugging - Scaffold a new project or files - Configure and generate tests - Generate code documentation - Improve your productivity in VS Code # For more information: - See here for setup instructions - Contact/Expert: Jason Baumgartner - Stack Overflow: View tagged items (or search by "GitHub Copilot" instead) - Website: GitHub Copilot in VS Code - Installation: [Install the GitHub Copilot extension](vscode:extension/GitHub.copilot) (this also installs the GitHub Copilot Chat extension)

title: Opsgenie

widgets.markdown: # What is it? You may or may not have heard of Opsgenie. Chances are, if you did, you heard that it is an “on call” or “alert notification” tool mostly used to alert people of issues after hours. In reality, that’s just a small part of what it can do. Even if there is no need for after-hours alerting, Opsgenie is able to provide tremendous value for most teams. Some of the bullet point benefits are: - Immediately reduce noise associated with multiple monitoring tools, applications, and systems - Allows events and alarms to be consolidated, categorized, deduplicated and prioritized - Notify ONLY the correct people, at the correct time, via the right channel - Everything is recorded and able to be reported and analyzed *“Well that’s great but this old application I support won’t be able to integrate with that!”* - **Wrong!** We have yet to find anything that can’t. If it can send an email, call an API, run an external CLI command, run a script, or make an https REST request, it can be integrated. If you’d like to learn a little more, here is a very brief (2 minute, 40 second) video answering “What's Opsgenie?” If you want to dive into specifics on several different topics, this playlist has several videos on different topics that may answer some of those questions. This is also an excellent resource if your team is going to start implementation. Contact the Site Reliability Engineering Team if you have questions about getting started. # For more information: - Contact/Expert: #IS -Site Reliability Engineering - Connect with other developers: Opsgenie User Group - How-to Guide: Getting Started with Opsgenie (Documentation/New User/How-to) - Stack Overflow: View tagged items (or search by "Opsgenie" instead) - Percipio: Training

widgets.markdown: # What is it? OutSystems is a low-code development platform that enables acceleration of development for reactive web and mobile applications. Using diagramming and flowcharting studio tooling, application screens, logic flow, and database access ideas can be quickly converted into .NET code that runs on a cluster of servers partitioned into functionally distinct environments without in-depth .NET experience. O11 is the on-premises platform utilized at Federated (ODC is the cloud-native service-based offering you might read about that we do not use). There is alignment and integration with existing systems, as well as facilitated management of backend resources. Analytics and reporting is available through the platform’s administrative tooling. For standing up a UI or rapid-prototyping a basic application, OutSystems is best-in-slot. For enterprise-grade monolithic business applications, careful and early requirement analysis with project stakeholders, platform experts, and technical architects is strongly advised to avoid costly technical debt accumulation. # For more information: - Contact/Expert: #IS -OutSystems Support - Connect with other developers: OutSystems User Group - Screen Design support: #IS -Screen Design Team - External/Mobile App pen testing: #IS -Risk and Compliance - Stack Overflow: View tagged items (search by "OutSystems" instead, or consider starting with the OutSystems Best Practices document) - Website: OutSystems Support - ServiceNow: Software Request (*Software = OutSystems Service Studio*) - Percipio: OutSystems Journey - Service Center: - DEV - BETA - STAGE - PROD - INF - EDUC1 - EDUC2 - Role Mapper: - DEV - BETA - STAGE - PROD (read only) - INF - EDUC1 - EDUC2 - Lifetime

widgets.markdown: # What is it? Of all the operations done in an ETL process the E or Extract is the most repetitive and open for automation. Moving data from one spot to another typically requires little intervention from end users. For those reasons it was decided that a tool that could automate this process was necessary, and so the Simple On-Demand Load Automation Resource - SOLAR - application development was started. SOLAR lowers the barrier to entry for any team that just needs to get a snapshot of their data for reporting purposes and doesn't need to do any transformations on the extract. # For more information: - Contact/Expert: #IS -Data Platform - Connect with other developers: SOLAR User Group - EDT Wiki: SOLAR - Configuration: SOLAR Navigator - Stack Overflow: View tagged items (or search by "SOLAR" instead)

widgets.markdown: # What is it? SonarQube is Federated’s static code analysis tool designed to help developers detect and fix coding issues across more than 30 programming languages and frameworks. By integrating with your continuous integration (CI) pipeline, it performs automatic reviews of code to identify bugs, vulnerabilities, and code smells, ensuring that our code meets the standards set in our quality gates. Using SonarQube allows for immediate feedback on code quality which helps keep our codebase healthy and maintainable. SonarQube Features: - Pipeline Quality Gates - Top Tier Analysis and Speed - Shared, Unified Configurations and Rules - SonarLint IDE Plugins (STS and VSCode) - Viewable Code Quality Metrics # For more information: - Contact/Expert: #IS -ADOSupportTeam - Link: SonarQube Federated Projects - Vendor Website: SonarQube - Stack Overflow: View tagged items (or search by "SonarQube" instead)

title: WSRR - DataPower

widgets.markdown: # What is it? WebSphere Service Registry and Repository (WSRR) provides functionality for both storage and retrieval of data tied to web services. It offers greater capabilities tied to Services than just a documentation basis. It allows for searchability, knowledge of consumers, versioning and other capabilities. WSRR, in conjunction with an intermediary (DataPower) and trust zone setups, also provides security and reporting/statistics. # For more information: - Contact/Expert: #IS-BPM Programming - Stack Overflow Community: DataPower and WSRR Community - Stack Overflow: View tagged items (search by "WSRR" instead) - Training: WSRR Training - WSRR Quick Link: WSRR Governance - DataPower Quick Links: - Prod: BPM Toolbox | Log Location = \\\syslogs.fedins.com\Syslogs\hosts\services-prod - Dev: BPM Toolbox | Log Location = \\\syslogs.fedins.com\Syslogs\hosts\services-dev - Beta: BPM Toolbox | Log Location = \\\syslogs.fedins.com\Syslogs\hosts\services-beta - Educ: BPM Toolbox | Log Location = \\\syslogs.fedins.com\Syslogs\hosts\services-educ - DataPower Operations Dashboard: DPOD (see also User Guide)
